Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
set_path_adjust_group(25.10)                      set_path_adjust_group(25.10)

Name
       set_path_adjust_group  - Allows you to specify the path that is used by
       the set_path_adjust command for setting path slack adjustment values

Syntax
       set_path_adjust_group

       [-help]

       -name <<path_adjust_group_name>>

       [-from <<from_list>>]

       [-to <<to_list>>]

       [-through <<through_list>>]

       Allows you to specify the path that is used by the set_path_adjust com-
       mand for setting path slack adjustment values.

       The set_path_adjust_group command is not allowed to be used inside  the
       SDC constraints file. It is only allowed in the tool run script.

       If   path   group   definitions   are  matching/overlapping  (when  the
       -from/-through/-to parameters are used), then path group  resetting  is
       applied.  The path group overwriting and prioritization rules are simi-
       lar to path exceptions.

       For more details, refer to group_path.

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage.

       -from <<from_list>>
              Specifies a list of pins, instances,  or  clocks  that  are  the
              start of the paths.

       -name <<path_adjust_group_name>>
              Specifies the name of the path adjust group.

       -through <<through_list>>
              Specifies  a  list  of  pins  or  instances  where  the paths go
              through.

       -to <<to_list>>
              Specifies a list of pins, instances, or clocks  where  the  path
              ends.

Examples
       The following commands specify the adjusted path groups:

              * set_path_adjust_group  -name AG1 -from in1 -through buf1/A -to
                out1

              * set_path_adjust_group  -name  AG2   -from   [get_clocks   CK1]
                -through buf1/A -to [get_clocks CK2]

              * set_path_adjust_group  -name  AG3 -from [get_clocks {CK1 CK2}]
                -to [get_clocks {CK1 CK2}]

Related Information
